<h3>My First JavaScript</h3>
<button type="button"
onclick="document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML = Date()">
Click me to display Date and Time.</button>

<p id="demo">This is a time demonstration. & JavaScript can change the style of an HTML element</p>

<div>
<p id="db">JavaScript can change the style of an HTML element.</p>

<script>
function myFunction() {
  document.getElementById("db").style.fontSize = "25px"; 
  document.getElementById("db").style.color = "red";
  document.getElementById("db").style.backgroundColor = "yellow";        
}
</script>

<button type="button" onclick="myFunction()">Click Me!</button>

</div>


<div>
	<p>Here, a JavaScript changes the value of the src (source) attribute of an image.</p>

<script>
function light(sw) {
  var pic;
  if (sw == 0) {
    pic = "I:/HTML/image/pic_bulboff.gif"
  } else {
    pic = "I:/HTML/image/pic_bulbon.gif"
  }
  document.getElementById('myImage').src = pic;
}
</script>

<img id="myImage" src="I:\HTML\image\pic_bulboff.gif" width="100" height="180">

<p>
<button type="button" onclick="light(1)">Light On</button>
<button type="button" onclick="light(0)">Light Off</button>
</p>

</div>

